{
  "stem": "27340.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And th-- th-- this bloody German dug his hands into there and threw everything out of there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know what he was suspecting we were smuggling or what.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He found nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, good.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And now, of course, the problem was how the hell can I pack all this into there again?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my brother and I stuffed underwear and socks into coat pockets, on top of everything else.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were basically like scarecrows walking around, you know, like this, because we, we could hardly sort of keep our arms to one side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Th-there was too much sort of textile material between us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We must have looked like scarecrows.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But somehow, we managed to get across here.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Holland, of course, there was a wonderful reception by relief organizations, Jewish and non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then when we got to [INAUDIBLE], there was a similar sort of a reception again by totally interdenominational people who meant well, who were obviously caring, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And ultimately, we got to London.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in London, we were met-- that's my brother and I, we were extremely fortunate-- by my aunt and uncle.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Middlebrook, Sam and Lenny Middlebrook, who lived in London.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they took us to their home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And ultimately, they felt it would be better if we were with other children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had no children of their own.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we were sent to a hostel for refugee children that was run-- this particular one-- was run by B'nai B'rith and was, in fact, the Margate in Kent, right.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, right by the sea.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
